PN,46902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1778097963
OL,3,CPlaid Cymru on course to be largest
OL,4,Cparty in the Senedd according to
OL,5,Clatest poll
OL,7,FAccording to MRP modelling by YouGov
OL,8,Ffor ITV Cymru Wales in partnership
OL,9,Fwith Cardiff University, under the new
OL,10,Fd'Hondt voting system, this round of
OL,11,Fresults means Plaid Cymru would win 43
OL,12,Fseats and Reform would take 34.
OL,14,FAlthough this is just one scenario, it
OL,15,Fdemonstrates how a small vote share
OL,16,Fincrease can have a huge impact on
OL,17,Fprojected seats in this new electoral
OL,18,Fsystem.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,495,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1778097963
OL,3,CPlaid Cymru on course to be largest
OL,4,Cparty in the Senedd according to
OL,5,Clatest poll
OL,7,FLabour has continued the trend of
OL,8,Fpolling in third place, at 12%, which
OL,9,Fwould again yield 12 seats, but not
OL,10,Ffor Welsh leader Eluned Morgan.
OL,12,FThe Welsh Conservatives have seen a
OL,13,Fmodest increase in their vote share at
OL,14,F9% placing them in fourth which would
OL,15,Ftranslate into four seats.
OL,17,FThe Green Party has dropped into fifth
OL,18,Fplace at 8% which in this round of
OL,19,Fresults would only net them two seats
OL,20,Fin Caerdydd Ffynnon Taf and Caerdydd
OL,21,FPenarth.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,495,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1778097963
OL,3,CPlaid Cymru on course to be largest
OL,4,Cparty in the Senedd according to
OL,5,Clatest poll
OL,7,FHowever, Labour, the Conservatives and
OL,8,Fthe Greens are all polling with a
OL,9,Flevel of vote share that, with just a
OL,10,Ffew percentage points difference
OL,11,Feither way, would have a huge impact
OL,12,Fon the number of seats won within
OL,13,Fconstituencies, and then across Wales.
OL,15,FThe drop in the number of Green seats
OL,16,Fcould be completely reversed if just a
OL,17,Ffew thousand more votes go their way
OL,18,Facross the constituencies they are
OL,19,Fmost competitive in, but not currently
OL,20,Fprojected to pick up the sixth seat.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
