FL,495,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1778097963
OL,3,CPlaid Cymru on course to be largest
OL,4,Cparty in the Senedd according to
OL,5,Clatest poll
OL,7,FThe Welsh Lib Dems have held at 6%
OL,8,Fwhich, in this scenario, would elect
OL,9,Fleader Jane Dodds in Brycheiniog Tawe
OL,10,FNedd.
OL,12,FAlongside voting intentions, more than
OL,13,Ffour in ten (43%) respondents think
OL,14,Fthat Plaid Cymru will end up leading
OL,15,Fthe next Welsh government.
OL,17,FThis is by far the most popular
OL,18,Fopinion. By comparison, only 15% think
OL,19,Fthat Reform UK will lead the next
OL,20,FWelsh government and they were the
OL,21,Fsecond largest party selected.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,495,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1778097963
OL,3,CPlaid Cymru on course to be largest
OL,4,Cparty in the Senedd according to
OL,5,Clatest poll
OL,7,FThe poll also found people in Wales
OL,8,Fwould prefer the next government to be
OL,9,Fformed by a single party (44%) instead
OL,10,Fof a coalition of multiple parties
OL,11,F(32%).
OL,13,FWhen asked "If you had to say, what is
OL,14,Fthe single biggest factor influencing
OL,15,Fyour vote in the upcoming Senedd
OL,16,Felection?" the most popular answers
OL,17,Fwere "Stopping Reform" and
OL,18,F"Immigration".
OL,26,@uD@LOUxD@JO]yD@FOUyD@VO]zD@AOUzD@MO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/11
